reviews.review_text: Good Stuff I loved a tape of this show I had waaaaay back. The enjoyment was mostly based on the monster Sugaree that kicks of this show. Not a bad show overall but nothing overly exciting other than it taking place in Alaska. Good soundboard copy.

Northern Dead Nice Playing, and Terrapin. And somehow the show feels- touched with the Far North! You can feel the crowd, so psyched to see them, be it local, or flew ( drove? hope not!) in deadheads, or- local rock fans about to have their minds blown!
4 stars includes the venue's added energy.

Brokedown Palace Location, Location! Location.
In the Middle of Sugar Magnolia
the polar ice caps begin MELTING!
